			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2017</a> paper:</span><br><i>Metacasanova: an optimized meta-compiler for domain-specific languages</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/FrancescoDiGiacomo.html">Francesco Di Giacomo</a>, <a href="../profile/MohamedAbbadi.html">Mohamed Abbadi</a>, <a href="../profile/AgostinoCortesi.html">Agostino Cortesi</a>, <a href="../profile/PieterSpronck.html">Pieter Spronck</a>, <a href="../profile/GiuseppeMaggiore.html">Giuseppe Maggiore</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3136014.3136015">10.1145/3136014.3136015</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4c.html"><span class="tagM">T4C: Vertical Transformation</span></a><ul><li> Metacasanova is a meta-compiler for DSLs, focusing on compilation/code generation pipelines.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> It targets domain-specific languages and their efficient compilation.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5f.html"><span class="tagL">T5F: Performance</span></a><ul><li> The contribution emphasizes optimization and efficiency of the generated artifacts/toolchain.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> As a meta-compiler, it is tooling infrastructure for implementing DSLs.
</li></ul></li></ul>
